// ===========================================================================
// main.cu — entry point for project 29.05
//           Ultrasound: GPU beamforming (plane-wave delay-and-sum B-mode)
//
// EDUCATIONAL / SYNTHETIC ONLY (CLAUDE.md paragraph 1, 8, and the medical-
// robotics rule in paragraph 8): every scatterer this program images comes
// from a numerical phantom generated by scripts/make_synthetic.py — never
// patient data — and nothing this program prints or writes is a diagnostic
// or therapeutic claim. This project teaches ultrasound SIGNAL PROCESSING
// (beamforming), not medicine.
//
// What this program does, start to finish
// -----------------------------------------
//   1. Load the committed array/pulse/phantom-region parameters
//      (data/sample/array_params.csv, cross-checked against kernels.cuh —
//      the 03.01 pattern) and the point-scatterer phantom
//      (data/sample/phantom.csv: 9 wire targets + a high-scattering
//      inclusion + background speckle scatterers).
//   2. SYNTHESIZE the channel data: for every scatterer and every array
//      element, the exact two-way pulse-echo time-of-flight, a Gaussian-
//      windowed carrier pulse, 1/r receive-spreading falloff, and thermal
//      noise (host-only, deterministic — the project's SYNTHETIC SENSOR,
//      not the taught algorithm; see the header comment in kernels.cuh).
//   3. GPU PIPELINE (the taught algorithm, three stages):
//        das_kernel -> quadrature_demod_kernel -> envelope_lowpass_kernel
//        -> log_compress_kernel                      (kernels.cu)
//   4. CPU PIPELINE: das_cpu -> envelope_detect_cpu -> log_compress_cpu
//      (reference_cpu.cpp), on the IDENTICAL channel data.
//   5. VERIFY STAGE (the §5 GPU-vs-CPU gate, three sub-checks): the
//      beamformed RF image, the envelope, and the final dB image must each
//      agree between the two pipelines within a documented tolerance.
//   6. FOUR ANALYTIC / KNOWN-TRUTH gates (the physics made measurable):
//        (i)   LOCALIZATION — every wire target's image peak must land
//              within one resolution cell of its true position.
//        (ii)  RESOLUTION — the isolated center wire's measured -6 dB
//              lateral/axial point-spread-function width must match the
//              derived lambda*F# / (cycles*lambda/2) formulas within a
//              documented factor.
//        (iii) CONTRAST — the inclusion's mean dB must exceed the
//              background speckle's mean dB by a documented margin.
//        (iv)  DELAY_CHECK — the DAS delay formula, evaluated for one
//              known (pixel, element) pair, must equal an independently
//              re-derived closed-form two-way time within float tolerance.
//   7. Artifacts: demo/out/bmode.pgm (the B-mode image, wire peaks marked)
//      and demo/out/psf_profile.csv (the isolated wire's lateral/axial
//      dB profiles — the resolution measurement, plottable).
//
// Output contract (load-bearing!): stable lines are "[demo]", "PROBLEM:",
// "SCENARIO:", "VERIFY:", "LOCALIZATION:", "RESOLUTION:", "CONTRAST:",
// "DELAY_CHECK:", "ARTIFACT:", "RESULT:" — "[info]"/"[time]" are NOT diffed
// (device names and measured margins vary by machine/GPU architecture,
// same reasoning as 08.01/03.01). Change a stable line -> update
// demo/expected_output.txt in the same change.
//
// Read this first, then kernels.cuh -> kernels.cu -> reference_cpu.cpp.
// ===========================================================================

